HEADWORD: Saprophagan
<hw>Sa*proph"a*gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sapro`s</grk> rotten + <grk>fagei^n</grk> to eat: cf. F.
<ets>saprophage</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a tribe of
beetles which feed upon decaying animal and vegetable substances; a
carrion beetle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saprophagous</ent>⟦br⟧
